          <change when="2017-08-09T18:26:01+02:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/users/JacquesBromberg">Submit - Added metadata and Greek text from O. Claud 2.410, NY workshop. I made the following alterations to the published edition:&#xD;
Line 1: Edition prints “ι̣” as initial letter, but it looks like “ν̣”. Edition reads “ὀριφανῆ”, mistaking the down-stroke from “φ” in line above for an “ι”, but resulting word is very difficult to explain. We clearly should read “ὀρφανὴ” instead, which makes far better sense alongside “ὦ πά̣τ̣ερ ποθούμενε” in line 2. Edition reads “σαί”, when ostracon pretty clearly has “καὶ”. Edition does not recognize end of line, which contains several readable characters (μα̣ν….ο).&#xD;
Line 3: Edition does not recognize end of line, which contains clear “τὴν̣” plus at least one more lost letter.&#xD;
Line 4: Again, edition prints “ι̣” as initial letter, but it looks much more like “ν̣”. Edition does not recognize vacat following λυργάν and traces of at least one more letter.&#xD;</change>
